<HL>
   Ark Restaurants Buys Shares
</HL>
<DATE>
05/17/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B8
</SO>
<CO>
   RK
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Ark Restaurants Corp. said it agreed to
purchase 380,000 shares, or about 11% of its common stock
from Ernest Bogen, chairman, for $3.25 a share.
   The company said Mr. Bogen, who will retain 10,000 shares,
will remain chairman. At the same time, it said he will also
work on special projects as a consultant.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In composite trading on the American Stock Exchange
yesterday, Ark's shares closed at $3.12, down 12 cents.
   Ark owns or operates 20 restaurants and bars in New York,
Boston and Washington, D.C.
</TEXT>
